location.city_name: サンリオピューロランド Sanrio Puroland

social_posts.post_text:
Big day of characters activities!!! 🥹🐰💕 We went to Sanrio Puroland in the day & the Pokémon Café/Center at night!! Both places are definitely designed for children 🤣 but there’s still lots to enjoy!

At Puroland they had a traditional Kabuki x Hello Kitty theatre performance & it was fantastic!!! (Again no photos or videos were allowed 🥲) But it was such a cute & fresh way to take in a traditional dance style! 

As for the Pokémon Café - I recommend just going for dessert & drinks 🍰 The main meals were very mediocre & very expensive 🤣😭🤣😭 But an extremely large Gengar came out at the end (so large he had to shuffle sideways into the room 🤣) & did a performance which was very sweet & ended with him cutting the power in the restaurant 👻

And of course I couldn’t wait to wear my new (vintage) @louisvuitton bag from @atlantisvintagetokyo!!! 🤗 I’m so glad my video about Atlantis has reached so many people & introduced you all to Yuji!!! 🙏🏻 I couldn’t recommend shopping with them for your next Tokyo trip more 😌😌😌🛍️💖 I will definitely be going back again during this trip 😝

2 weeks was just the right amount of time - we were even able to have some rest days! We were doing 10-20k steps per day every day, so some days off were so essential 😮‍💨 Only just now am I starting to feel like I have enough stamina for all of the walking & stairs 🤣🤣

I want to recommend the hotel we stayed at! We had a bit of a mishap with Airbnb & the accomodation we booked originally was so dirty & dodgy 😭 So we had to find somewhere to stay last minute & stumbled across Section L Ginza East! 

If you've been to Tokyo before, you'll know that most of the accomodation is SO small! Ideally you want to find a room 20sqm+ which takes a lotttt of searching 🤣 At Section L we had a spacious apartment with a full closet, laundry area, bathroom & table with chairs! It's almost unheard of hahaha so I just wanted to share in case anyone was looking for somewhere good to stay - I highly recommend it! 🫶🏻

Now we are headed for Sapporo for a week in the snow before returning to Tokyo to stay at the Disney resort 🤭🤭🤭❤️🙏🏻

social_posts.post_text: It’s so hard to resist all of the miscellaneous junk that I absolutely do not need 😭😭😭
Happy to report that I was not cold!!!!! Another successful day!!!! 😮‍💨🙏🏻☃️
I went to the new location that just opened in Sapporo, but they also have this in Tokyo, Kyoto & Osaka!!! 🥹🐷🩷🙏🏻☕️
I love snow so much 😭😭😭 (More than I love my beloved fluffy hat & Chanel bag it seems 😳)

It started snowing overnight in Sapporo!!!!! 🥹😭❄️🙏🏻🌨️ For our first two days here there was absolutely no snow, there wasn’t even old snow banked up on the streets 😳 Enduring temperatures below zero degrees without the reward of snow honestly feels like a punishment 🤣🤣

I’m so happy we’ve gotten a little bit of snow now - but I’ve learnt that the snowfall is getting less & less here every year & they have to ship in extra snow from elsewhere for their annual snow festival 😭😭 We will still visit every year but maybe we need to come a little bit later into the season! 

They’ve just opened up a @mipigcafe here in Sapporo, so of course we had to visit 🥹🥹🥹 I love cuddling all the little piggies!!! 🐷🩷 I also had the BEST facial of my life at @gracefiore_sapporo today - highly recommend if you’re in town 💆🏻‍♀️ They use pressure point techniques on your scalp to drain fluid & puffiness out of your face & it worked so unbelievably well!!!! 

Here’s hoping the snow keeps falling for the rest of our time in Sapporo 🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻☃️🤞🏻🍀
SO thrilled we woke up to snowfall this morning!!!! 🥹🙏🏻☃️🌨️❄️
I don’t know what it is about konbini food but I can eat an unlimited amount of it & never get full 🤣😭🤣😭

Nakajima Park is one of my favourite places in all of Sapporo 😌 It’s the most beautiful park filled with snow, trees, (frozen over) lakes, a temple & a war memorial. Both times we’ve gone it’s been almost deserted too - it’s so peaceful! Spending time like this in Sapporo after being in the midst of Tokyo for a few weeks is so good for the soul. 💆🏻‍♀️❤️❄️
I’m so jealous of ANYONE who got to grow up with snow 😭😭😭😭 Where I live we have one season only and it’s Summer 😭🤮😭🤮
I can’t believe how perfect for it this chain I had with me was!!! Thank you @atlantisvintagetokyo ily 🥹💖🙏🏻🇯🇵⭐️

I HAVE NEVER BEEN SO COLD IN MY ENTIRE LIFE 🤣😭🤣😭

We visited Otaru in Sapporo which is a beautiful little port town with canals running through the streets! It was such a charming place but it felt at least 100 degrees colder than in the city 🥶 The wind was so piercing & snow was coming down from every direction! A smarter woman would have at least worn pants 😑🤣

One of our favourite things to do whilst staying in Sapporo is to catch the train out to all of the little nearby towns. The scenery & architecture is so unlike anything at home, we could walk around & take it all in forever 😌❄️☃️ There’s also no lines out in the small towns 😮‍💨 (Japan is all about waiting in line 😝)
How I look in the last clip of the facial is the funniest thing I’ve ever seen 😭🤣😭🤣 The spa is @gracefiore_sapporo! 💕 I loved it so much I went back a second time!!! 🧖🏻‍♀️🫶🏻
I LOVE OCTOPUS BALLS 🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻🍺

The final day in Sapporo (before heading to the Disney resort for a few days!!!) 🥹🥹🥹

We visited Maruyama Park which is incredibly popular in the Spring time as one of the best places to view the cherry blossoms, but in the Winter time it looks straight out of a woodland Christmas card 🥹🎄✨ The forest here was so beautiful & had these little tree stump tables scattered about which made it feel like a fairy village! 

Inside the park, they also had the Maruyama Zoo. At the zoo they rescue injured animals & nurse them back to health/house them if they can’t survive in the wild ❤️‍🩹 The zoo was almost deserted, I’d say we ran into less than 20 people on the entire grounds! It was the best zoo experience I’ve ever had to be able to look at all the exhibits without any crowds, we accidentally stayed right up until it was time to close & they ushered us out 🤣🤣

Mamoru & his companions do not live at the zoo BTW 😝 Their owner has an adorable dog boutique that was around the corner from our hotel called @snobbishbabies_sapporo 🥹🩷✨ All of the dogs that live here get around wearing puffer jackets, boots & knit sweaters - it’s the cutest thing ever!!!

Now we’re flying back to Tokyo - the flight is about 1.5 hours & cost less than $100 FYI! Sapporo is such a special city, I hope you include it in your next Japan trip!!! ❤️❤️🙏🏻🇯🇵
I’ve clearly been missing out my whole life because I had no idea that hot lemonade was even a thing?!?! 😭😭😭
Checked into the Disney resort for the next 3 days!!!! 🤭🤭 Disney content is 🔛‼️‼️

Some snaps from DisneySea after dark! 🐬🤎✨

DisneySea is open until 9pm so we were able to spend some time there the night we arrived at the Disney resort 🤗🤗

The #1 question I have been asked is if you can only go to one, should it be Tokyo Disneyland or DisneySea?! Obviously the correct answer is both 😇 HOWEVER, if you can only go to one… I’m going to have to say Disneyland 🫣 Whilst DisneySea is a unique experience, I don’t think it has as much of the Disney magic & world building as Disneyland! On the other hand, it definitely has the better rides - but with good rides comes really really reallyyyy long lines 🫣😭 

This time I think we nailed the use of our time - a night at DisneySea & a full day at Disneyland is just the right amount for both parks! 🙏🏻

Also - did you know you can get married at Disneyland & have a full princess experience?! 🥹🥹🥹 That last photo is a real Belle bride, she looked so beautiful 😭 Last time we visited, I saw a Cinderella inspired bride too! 💐👰🏻‍♀️💕
THIS IS GOING TO BE THE BEST DAY EVER!!!!! 😮‍💨🙏🏻❤️
